<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="463" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,259,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,331,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Propodeum without wrinkles, with deep smooth anteromedian concavity. Fore wing vein 2m-cu strongly inclivous. Basal portion of first tarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[733,815,367,393]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly curved concave, inner profile with dense fine setae, spur reach to middle of concavity. Tergite 1 mat, with dense indistinct punctures. Mesopleuron, mesosternum, hind coxa and femur and tibia except subbase and apex slightly black, reddish brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="465" pageId="8" pageNumber="463" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,259,538]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,475,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Description</emphasis>
. Female (
<figureCitation box="[456,542,475,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
). Body length 3.4–4.0 mm. Fore wing length 
<quantity box="[1080,1221,475,502]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.35" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="3.2" pageId="8" pageNumber="463" unit="mm" value="3.35" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="3.2">3.2–3.5 mm</quantity>
. Ovipositor sheath length approximately 
<quantity box="[397,500,511,538]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="463" unit="mm" value="0.25">0.25 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
