<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,1830,2037]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1436,150,249]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="464" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,263,1830,1856]" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Head</emphasis>
. Face (
<figureCitation box="[346,427,1830,1856]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–24" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1723,1747]" captionTargetBox="[180,1420,564,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-143@8.[161,1427,561,1700]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–24. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 21 Habitus, lateral view 22 Head, anterior view 23 Head and pronotum, lateral view 24 Head and mesoscutum, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848343" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848343/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Fig. 22</figureCitation>
) 1.4 × as wide as long, slightly convex, with sparse brown setae; almost parallel laterally, smooth, shiny; upper margin with small indistinct median tubercle. Clypeal sulcus distinct. Anterior tentorial pit relatively small, upper margin distinctly below a line connecting lower margins of eyes. Clypeus strongly convex, texture as face, 1.7 × as wide as long, median portion of apical margin weakly arched forwardly. Mandible with two sharp teeth. Malar space 1.4 × as long as basal width of mandible. Subocular sulcus distinctly exist. Gena and vertex (
<figureCitation box="[238,341,2010,2036]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–4" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1768,1792]" captionTargetBox="[183,1419,631,1742]" captionTargetId="figure-176@2.[166,1420,631,1742]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–4. Megastylus (Dicolus) mentouense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Male. 1 Habitus, lateral view 2 Head, anterior view 3 Head, dorsal view 4 Head and pronotum, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848333" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848333/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="463">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
) shiny, posterior portion converging to occipital carina. Postocellar line 1.1 × as long as ocular- ocellar line. Antenna with 35–37 flagellomeres; flagellomeres with relatively longer setae. Ratio of length from first to fifth flagellomeres: 11.5:4.7:4.3:3.8:3.4. Occipital carina complete, joining hypostomal carina far above base of mandible.
</paragraph>
