<subSubSection box="[199,918,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1041]" box="[199,918,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific name is derived from the 
<typeStatus box="[773,821,799,825]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">type</typeStatus>
locality.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="465" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,151,1041]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Remarks</emphasis>
. The new species is similar to 
<emphasis box="[669,692,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiodte, 1838" authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1838" box="[708,1064,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megastylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentator" subGenus="Megastylus">
(
<emphasis box="[717,740,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[766,884,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">cruentator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schiodte, G." box="[894,1064,835,861]" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref6977" refString="Schiodte, G. (1838) Ichneumonidarum ad faunam Daniae pertinentium, genera et species novae. Revue Zoologique par la Societe Cuvierienne, 1, 139 - 141." type="journal article" year="1838">Schiødte, 1838</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1123,1146,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authority="Schiodte, 1838" authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1838" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megastylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbitator" subGenus="Megastylus">
(
<emphasis box="[1172,1195,835,860]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1221,1322,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">orbitator</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Schiodte, G." pageId="10" pageNumber="465" pagination="139 - 141" refId="ref6977" refString="Schiodte, G. (1838) Ichneumonidarum ad faunam Daniae pertinentium, genera et species novae. Revue Zoologique par la Societe Cuvierienne, 1, 139 - 141." type="journal article" year="1838">Schiødte, 1838</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from the latters by the following combination of characters: Propodeum with deep anteromedian transverse concavity; basal portion of first tarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[938,1022,907,933]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) strongly curved, inner profile with dense fine setae; mesoscutum, scutellum and propodeum entirely black. 
<emphasis box="[966,989,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1838" box="[1003,1178,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megastylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cruentator" subGenus="Megastylus">
(
<emphasis box="[1013,1036,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1060,1178,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">cruentator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1233,1256,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schiodte" authorityYear="1838" box="[1271,1428,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megastylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="465" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="orbitator" subGenus="Megastylus">
(
<emphasis box="[1280,1303,943,968]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">M</emphasis>
.) 
<emphasis box="[1327,1428,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">orbitator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: Propodeum without anteromedian concavity; basal portion of first tarsomere (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1136,979,1005]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–30" captionStartId="9.[151,264,1489,1513]" captionTargetBox="[162,1412,282,1456]" captionTargetId="figure-49@9.[162,1424,273,1466]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="FIGURES 25–30. Megastylus (Megastylus) yindianense Sheng &amp; Li, sp. nov. Holotype. Female. 25 Mesosoma, lateral view 26 Propodeum. 27 Front tibia and basal portion of tarsus, lateral view 28 Fore wing 29 Tergites 1–2, lateral view 30 Apical portion of metasoma, lateral view" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5848345" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5848345/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="465">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) not curved, inner profile without dense fine setae; mesoscutum, scutellum and propodeum at least partly brown or red brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
